quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to set the vertical alignment of all elements having class="test" to bottom:
[!raw!]
{0} {
   vertical-{1}: {2}
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The vertical-align Property [/h1]

The vertical-align property sets an element's vertical alignment. Commonly used values are [b]top[/b], [b]middle[/b], and [b]bottom[/b].

The example below shows how to vertically align the text between the table. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<table border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="height: 150px;">
  <tr>
     <td class="top">Top</td>
     <td class="middle">Middle</td>
     <td class="bottom">Bottom</td>
  </tr>
</table>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="522"]td.top {
   [b]vertical-align: top[/b];
}
td.middle {
   [b]vertical-align: middle[/b];
}
td.bottom {
   [b]vertical-align: bottom[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="3016" width="100%"]

[h1]The vertical-align Property[/h1]

The vertical-align property also takes the following values: [b]baseline[/b], [b]sub[/b], [b]super[/b], [b]%[/b] and [b]px [/b](or pt, cm). 
The example below shows the difference between them. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p>This is an <span class="baseline">inline text</span> example.</p>
<p>This is a <span class="sub">sub line text</span> example.</p>
<p> This is a <span class="super">super line text</span> example.</p>
<p> This is a <span class="pixel">pixel</span> example.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="523"]span.baseline {
    vertical-align: [b]baseline;[/b]
}
span.sub {
    vertical-align: [b]sub;[/b]
}
span.super {
    vertical-align: [b]super;[/b]
}
span.pixel {
    vertical-align: [b]-10px;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2599" width="100%"]
[note]Instead of [b]px[/b] values, you can use [b]pt[/b] (points), [b]cm [/b](centimeters) and [b]%[/b] (percentage) values.[/note]

[h1]The vertical-align Property[/h1]

Vertical align property does not act the same way for all elements.
For example, some additional CSS styling is needed for div elements. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<div class="main">
   <div class="paragraph">
   This text is aligned to the middle
   </div>
</div>[/code]
[b]The CSS: [/b] [code format="css" codeId="524"].main {
    height: 150px; width: 400px;
    background-color: LightSkyBlue;
    display: inline-table;
}
.paragraph {
    display: table-cell;
    vertical-align: middle;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b][img id="3022" width="100%"]
[note][b]display: inline-table; [/b]and[b] display: table-cell;[/b] styling rules are applied to make the vertical-align property work with divs.[/note]
